==English==

==Etymology==
From '''iso''', ''[[same]]'' + chronous, [[time]]


===Adjective===
'''isochronous'''
#{{computing}} of or pertaining to the use of the same clock throughout a network
#: ''Their entire national telephone network is isochronous, with a clock distribution tree radiating from a cesium clock.''
#{{computing}} of or pertaining to data associated with time sensitive application
#: ''These packets belong to an isochronous voice application and need priority handling.''